  "translations": {
    "en": "The Imam is the foremost of his time — no one comes close to him, no scholar equals him, no substitute is found for him, and none resemble or match him. He has been wholly specified with virtue, without seeking it or reaping it; rather, it is a specification from the Bestower of Virtue and Gifts. Who is it that reaches full recognition of the Imam or can subject him to their choosing? Far, far have the intellects strayed, the imaginations wandered, the minds bewildered, the eyes perplexed, the great ones diminished, the wise ones confused, the forbearing ones fallen short, the preachers confined, the intelligent ones become ignorant, the poets become speechless, the writers become incapable, and the rhetoricians unable to describe one quality of his qualities, or one virtue of his virtues. They acknowledge their inability and shortcoming. How can he be described in his essence, or how can one comprehend a thing of his matter, or find someone to take his place",
